"{\"uid\": \"nbcphiladelphia.com-paris-2024-summer-olympics-katie-ledecky-800m-freestyle-gold-2024-olympics-3932957\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Katie Ledecky swam to even more history onDay 8 of the 2024 Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 75, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TheTeam USAstar captured her fourth straightOlympictitle in the women's 800m freestyle event.\", \"from\": 77, \"to\": 170, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky won Saturday's final in8:11.04, fending off reigning silver medalist and second-place finisherAriarne Titmusof Australia (8:12.29).\", \"from\": 171, \"to\": 310, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 290, \"end\": 299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999770183970761, \"rank\": 1.605301587479474e-05, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stream Philadelphia News for free, 24/7, wherever you are with NBC10.\", \"from\": 312, \"to\": 381, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 319, \"end\": 331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philadelphia\", \"score\": 0.9949437219042625, \"rank\": 0.004801548278747349, \"text\": \"Philadelphia\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philadelphia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philadelphia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"AmericanPaige Maddencame in third (8:13.00) to earn her second medal of the Paris Games and third overall.\", \"from\": 383, \"to\": 489, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky, 27, joined Michael Phelps as the only swimmers to ever win Olympic gold four times in the same event.\", \"from\": 493, \"to\": 603, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 513, \"end\": 527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.588759404176287e-58, \"text\": \"Michael Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And with nine total gold medals, Ledecky is now tied with swimmer Mark Spitz, track star Carl Lewis, Soviet gymnast Larisa Latynina and Finnish runner Paavo Nurmi for second-most in Olympic history.\", \"from\": 604, \"to\": 802, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 670, \"end\": 680, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Spitz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mark Spitz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Spitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Spitz\"}, {\"begin\": 693, \"end\": 703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\"}, {\"begin\": 720, \"end\": 735, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Larisa Latynina\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\"}, {\"begin\": 740, \"end\": 747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Finland\", \"score\": 0.9993920739762999, \"rank\": 0.0005883572268353045, \"text\": \"Finnish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Finland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Finland\"}, {\"begin\": 755, \"end\": 766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paavo_Nurmi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paavo Nurmi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paavo_Nurmi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paavo_Nurmi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only Phelps, who claimed 23 Olympic golds in his legendary career, owns more.\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 881, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 809, \"end\": 815, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"score\": 0.9999999989361186, \"rank\": 1.0611842635913463e-09, \"text\": \"Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I put a lot of pressure on myself,\\\" Ledecky said.\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 933, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am just really happy that I could get the job done.\", \"from\": 934, \"to\": 988, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I knew that it was gonna be a tough race and I felt confident coming into it.\", \"from\": 990, \"to\": 1068, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I knew it was going to be tough no matter what, all the way down to the finish.\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1152, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So I just had to stick in the race, trust myself, trust my training, trust that I know the hungry side of that.\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1264, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And, yeah, I am just kind of relieved.\\\"\", \"from\": 1265, \"to\": 1304, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky will leave Paris with a four-medal haul, bringing her career total up to 14.\", \"from\": 1308, \"to\": 1392, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1327, \"end\": 1332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999902995569, \"rank\": 9.700434936125306e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She won gold in the 800m and 1500m freestyles, silver in the 4x200m relay and bronze in the 400m free,becoming the most-decorated U.S. female Olympian of all timein the process.\", \"from\": 1393, \"to\": 1570, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1535, \"end\": 1543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999999408828, \"rank\": 5.916215235047103e-11, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The focus now shifts toward the 2028 Los Angeles Olympics, where Ledecky will have a chance to continue to add to her legacy on home soil -- should she compete.\", \"from\": 1572, \"to\": 1732, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I'd love to (compete in 2028), but it's not easy,\\\" Ledeckysaid.\", \"from\": 1734, \"to\": 1798, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I will take it year by year, and give it everything I have got for as long as I have left in me.\\\"\", \"from\": 1799, \"to\": 1897, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Associated Press contributed to this story.\", \"from\": 1899, \"to\": 1946, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1903, \"end\": 1919, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9786335233842899, \"rank\": 0.02183285566261616, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}]}"